 photometric redshift accuracy. We find that a training set of\n\\textgreater 30 per cent of total sample size, provides little additional\nconstraint on the photometric redshifts, and note that our GP formalism\nstrongly outperforms ANNz in the sparse data regime for the simulated data set.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 20 May 2015 19:08:54 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 26 Aug 2015 22:46:51 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Mon, 19 Oct 2015 16:43:19 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-11-25"}
