\nstrongest starburst located within the central $\\sim$150 pc is responsible for\nthe ionization of the gas out to at least $\\sim$1 kpc. The gradual dilution of\nthe radiation with increasing distance from the center reflects the gradual and\ncontinuous transition from the highly ionized H II regions in the proximity of\nthe major starburst into the diffuse ionized gas.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 20 May 2015 22:01:57 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 31 Aug 2015 09:58:25 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-10-21"}
